WEBVTT

00:00.250 --> 00:01.650
<i>Amy:</i>
<i>Previously on "Heartland":</i>

00:01.704 --> 00:03.539
How come you didn't tell me
you're moving to Nashville?

00:03.606 --> 00:05.440
I didn't think
you'd care.

00:05.508 --> 00:06.575
Amy: We're bringing the
horses to Heartland.

00:06.643 --> 00:08.243
Mr. Hanley asked me
to care for them

00:08.310 --> 00:10.110
and I'm going to do that.

00:10.178 --> 00:11.812
You're gonna have to look after
more than just horses.

00:11.880 --> 00:12.880
(Dog whines)

00:15.216 --> 00:16.417
Miranda, you think
you're gonna win,

00:16.484 --> 00:17.752
but you're not.

00:17.819 --> 00:21.121
Put the boy before yourself,
for once,

00:21.189 --> 00:22.957
'cause I'm gonna fight you!
I'll fight you...

00:23.025 --> 00:24.324
I'll fight you
right to the end.

00:27.495 --> 00:28.295
♪

00:31.032 --> 00:32.731
(Spartan grunts and snorts)

00:32.800 --> 00:34.301
(Cell phone rings)

00:37.939 --> 00:39.039
Amy:
Good morning.

00:39.107 --> 00:40.574
Ty:
Hey. Good morning.

00:40.641 --> 00:42.175
Amy: Well, how are the
overnight guests doing?

00:42.242 --> 00:43.976
<i>Ty:</i>
<i>Ah, pretty good.</i>

00:44.044 --> 00:45.144
Skeeter made it
through the night

00:45.212 --> 00:47.046
without chewing
on his sutures.

00:47.114 --> 00:49.648
(Laughs)
Well, that's progress.

00:49.716 --> 00:51.050
<i>Ty:</i> <i>Yeah, I think I'm
starting</i> <i>to go crazy though,</i>

00:51.118 --> 00:52.552
being in this clinic
for over twenty-four hours.

00:52.619 --> 00:55.821
Well, how about I come by
in a little bit?

00:55.889 --> 00:57.423
Yeah,
that'd be awesome.

00:57.491 --> 00:58.490
Okay.
I should run,

00:58.558 --> 00:59.524
but I'll talk to you later.

00:59.592 --> 01:00.625
Okay, bye.

01:02.261 --> 01:03.695
All right, Lobo,
come on!

01:03.762 --> 01:06.498
Let's go get some breakfast!
Come on!

01:06.566 --> 01:08.633
What would you say
if I raised my babysitting fees

01:08.701 --> 01:10.502
to twenty-five dollars
an hour?

01:10.570 --> 01:13.171
Lou: I would say you're pricing
yourself out of the market.

01:13.239 --> 01:14.505
But that's how much
I need

01:14.573 --> 01:16.240
if I'm gonna be renting
an apartment in Hudson.

01:16.308 --> 01:17.541
An apartment?

01:17.609 --> 01:18.875
Yeah, just a one room,
or a bachelor,

01:18.943 --> 01:19.977
but it has to have
a dishwasher.

01:20.044 --> 01:21.412
I'm gonna take
a wild guess

01:21.480 --> 01:22.946
that you haven't talked
to your parents about this?

01:23.014 --> 01:25.048
No, because I'm never
talking to them again.

01:25.117 --> 01:26.484
Mallory, maybe moving
to Nashville

01:26.551 --> 01:27.684
won't be so bad.

01:27.752 --> 01:29.620
You should think of it
as an adventure.

01:29.687 --> 01:31.854
Going to Bora Bora
is an adventure.

01:31.922 --> 01:33.689
Moving to Nashville
is the worst thing

01:33.757 --> 01:35.125
that's happened to me--
Ever.

01:35.192 --> 01:36.259
And that's saying a lot

01:36.327 --> 01:37.927
considering I've fallen
into a well.

01:37.995 --> 01:39.295
Amy:
Good morning.

01:39.363 --> 01:40.796
<i>Mallory:</i>
<i>There's nothing good about it.</i>

01:40.864 --> 01:42.332
<i>(Lobo pants heavily)</i>
<i>U: Oh! No way. Muddy paws;</i>

01:42.399 --> 01:44.467
I just washed
this kitchen floor.

01:44.535 --> 01:45.901
Plus, he's always trying
to eat Katie's food

01:45.969 --> 01:47.002
off of her tray.

01:47.069 --> 01:48.604
Yeah,
but Katie loves him.

01:48.671 --> 01:51.340
Don't you, Katie?
Hmm?

01:51.407 --> 01:54.309
<i>Lou:</i> <i>He's cute, but he's
going</i> <i>outside where he belongs.</i>

01:54.377 --> 01:56.245
Can I borrow
five thousand dollars?

01:56.312 --> 01:57.513
Excuse me?

01:57.580 --> 01:58.947
Never mind.

01:59.015 --> 02:00.415
Lou: You know, if Lobo
won't sleep outside,

02:00.483 --> 02:02.216
you should ask Grandpa
to like build him a dog house

02:02.284 --> 02:03.184
or something.

02:03.252 --> 02:04.652
Where is Grandpa
anyway?

02:04.719 --> 02:06.487
Ah! Refer to the very
informative note

02:06.555 --> 02:08.455
on the fridge.

02:08.524 --> 02:11.292
"Be back later
this afternoon. Grandpa."

02:11.360 --> 02:12.660
Yeah, and I'm pretty sure
I heard his truck

02:12.727 --> 02:15.296
leaving the yard around
midnight last night.

02:15.364 --> 02:16.430
Midnight;

02:16.498 --> 02:17.931
That doesn't seem
like Grandpa.

